## 7. Shared shell behavior across public pages

Every public page must be composed from the same macro structure:

1. Announcement or slim utility bar (optional, configurable)
2. Header / primary navigation
3. Hero block
4. Main content sections
5. Conversion block
6. Footer

This structure should feel stable across all top-level public routes.

## 7.1 Header behavior
Header must:
- be sticky after scroll
- reduce height slightly on scroll
- preserve clear CTA visibility
- support desktop dropdowns and mobile drawer
- use active-state highlighting
- include keyboard-accessible navigation
- preserve contrast against hero background

## 7.2 Mobile navigation
Use a full-height drawer or panel, not a cramped dropdown.

Must include:
- primary nav items
- expandable sub-sections
- top CTA
- secondary CTA if useful
- member login/access route
- close icon + overlay dismissal

## 7.3 Hero construction rules
Heroes should follow the template's pattern:
- bold left-side message
- supporting copy
- CTA cluster
- visual support zone on the right or behind
- accent-backed content container
- trust signal nearby

Do not place huge amounts of copy in the hero.

Hero copy formula:
- eyebrow
- short punchy heading
- one paragraph
- primary CTA
- secondary CTA
- optional proof strip or micro-stat row

