## 20. Data-state and system-state UX

This is where builders usually get lazy and the product looks half-finished. Do not do that.

## 20.1 Loading states
Every list page and detail page must have proper skeletons.

### List skeleton
- title placeholder
- filter row placeholder
- 6 to 9 card placeholders

### Detail skeleton
- breadcrumb placeholder
- hero text block placeholder
- media/sidebar placeholder
- body section placeholders

## 20.2 Empty states
Every listing/search/filter state must support:
- no results found
- category empty
- access restricted
- content coming soon

Each empty state should provide a recovery path:
- clear filters
- browse related items
- compare membership
- contact support
- request help

## 20.3 Error states
Error pages or blocks must:
- explain what failed
- allow retry
- offer fallback navigation
- not dump raw technical errors into the UI

## 20.4 Not found behavior
404 pages should stay on-brand and help users navigate back into:
- DocShare
- Knowledge Center
- Services
- Membership
- Home

