## 21. Accessibility requirements

Firebase Studio must treat accessibility as core build quality, not optional cleanup.

## 21.1 Minimum standard
Target WCAG 2.2 AA.

## 21.2 Required behaviors
- visible focus ring on all interactive elements
- keyboard navigation across header, drawers, accordions, tabs, filters
- semantic headings
- landmark usage
- descriptive button/link labels
- sufficient contrast
- reduced-motion support
- form error association
- alt text support for meaningful imagery
- no information conveyed by color alone

## 21.3 Content readability rules
- maximum comfortable text line length for body content
- adequate paragraph spacing
- bullet lists where scanning matters
- avoid giant dense walls of text on knowledge pages

---

## 22. Performance and implementation quality

The visual polish should not come at the cost of a sluggish mess.

## 22.1 Performance requirements
- optimize image sizes
- lazy load offscreen media
- avoid heavy animation libraries if not needed
- keep critical above-the-fold content fast
- prefer reusable, lightweight components
- avoid shipping giant icon packs if only a subset is needed

## 22.2 Technical build preference
Build pages with:
- shared layout shells
- reusable section components
- clear content contracts
- consistent token usage
- no hard-coded magic numbers scattered everywhere

## 22.3 Image handling
Use a consistent aspect-ratio system:
- hero visual
- card thumbnail
- logo strip
- content preview
- knowledge article media

Do not allow irregular image shapes to break layout rhythm.

---

## 23. SEO and metadata requirements

Public pages must support clean metadata.

## 23.1 Required metadata
- title
- description
- open graph image
- canonical URL
- structured breadcrumbs where useful
- article metadata for knowledge detail pages
- organization/service metadata where applicable

## 23.2 URL rules
- lowercase slugs
- short readable paths
- no unnecessary nesting
- no temporary placeholder route names in production

